rbbProvMIB.name: rbbProvMIB
rbbProvMIB.contactinfo: Randy Turner Postal: 2Wire, Inc. 694 Tasman Dr. Milpitas, CA 95035 Tel: 408-895-1216 Fax: 408-428-9590 E-mail: rturner@2wire.com
rbbProvMIB.description: This is the MIB Module for provisioning of broadband customer premises equipment, specifically xDSL-related services. While not precluding other broadband technology, the MIB has been constructed around existing xDSL facilities, including ATM transports.

RBBServiceID.name: RBBServiceID
RBBServiceID.description: A globally unique OID that unambiguously specifies a particular service, and as much protocol and semantics as is necessary to access the service

RBBServiceName.name: RBBServiceName
RBBServiceName.description: A string denoting the same information as RBBServiceOID, except this object is in human-readable form.

RBBServiceProvider.name: RBBServiceProvider
RBBServiceProvider.description: A human-readable string representing the name of the private or public entity that is making the service available. For a typical internet service provider (ISP), this would be the name of the ISP company itself

RBBServiceStatus.name: RBBServiceStatus
RBBServiceStatus.description: An enumeration representing the current state of a particular service availability or service subscription (i.e., up, down, enabled, etc.)

RBBURLType.name: RBBURLType
RBBURLType.description: An octet string containing a uniform resource locator (URL). The usage of this URL is object- context dependent. See individual object descriptions that reference this textual convention

RBBCPEAuthType.name: RBBCPEAuthType
RBBCPEAuthType.description: An opaque string used to identify a particular subscriber. Currently, this MIB does not specify how authentication strings are generated. This is still an open issue.

RBBMailAddr.name: RBBMailAddr
RBBMailAddr.description: The email address (user@domain) of a contact that is responsible for some entity that references this textual convention, such as the administrator for an access network, or the email address of the admin for a particular service provider

RBBCPESerialNumber.name: RBBCPESerialNumber
RBBCPESerialNumber.description: Define the syntax of a product serial number

RBBVendorModel.name: RBBVendorModel
RBBVendorModel.description: Define the syntax of a CPE vendor model

srvServicesTable.name: srvServicesTable
srvServicesTable.description: This table contains a sequence of rows where each row describes a particular service that is available to a broadband customer. The service availability expressed in this table is assumed to be valid only for customers served by this management infrastructure, and may differ on a regional basis, even within the same overall access network.

srvServiceEntry.name: srvServiceEntry
srvServiceEntry.description: This object defines the individual rows in the SRV services table (srvServicesTable)

srvServiceIdentifier.name: srvServiceIdentifier
srvServiceIdentifier.description: A unique object identifier (OID) value uniquely representing a particular service.

srvServiceName.name: srvServiceName
srvServiceName.description: A human-readable name string that identifies a service to an end-user

srvServiceProvider.name: srvServiceProvider
srvServiceProvider.description: A human-readable name string that identifies the public or private sponsoring entity for a particular service.

srvServiceStatus.name: srvServiceStatus
srvServiceStatus.description: An INTEGER enumeration describing the current availability status of a particular service. NOTE: This status implies different semantics than that used by srvServiceSubrStatus

srvServiceConnType.name: srvServiceConnType
srvServiceConnType.description: An enumerated value describing the type of endpoint address used to refer to a particular service, as well as whether the CPE should be an initiator or target during the connection.

srvServiceQOSType.name: srvServiceQOSType
srvServiceQOSType.description: The quality-of-service to be associated with a connection to a particular service.

srvServiceSpeedReq.name: srvServiceSpeedReq
srvServiceSpeedReq.description: The bandwidth or speed (in bits-per-second) necessary to realize a particular service

srvServiceLatencyReq.name: srvServiceLatencyReq
srvServiceLatencyReq.description: An enumerated value that describes whether or not a particular service has special latency requirements associated to effectively realize the service.

srvServiceURL.name: srvServiceURL
srvServiceURL.description: A URL string associated with a particular service. A service may be provisioned with an associated URL that can be used either as a provisioning link or as a potentially advertising source for the service.

srvServiceDescr.name: srvServiceDescr
srvServiceDescr.description: A human-readable string used to provide a brief description for a particular service.

srvAdminContact.name: srvAdminContact
srvAdminContact.description: A string representing the email address of an administrator contact for the particular service. This could either be a contact used to request new service or options associated with the service, OR, could be used as a support contact address for an existing subscription.

srvRowInfo.name: srvRowInfo
srvRowInfo.description: Maintains row status information for this table

rbbSubTable.name: rbbSubTable
rbbSubTable.description: This table contains a sequence of rows where each row describes a particular service subscription between an end-user CPE and a particular service.

rbbSubEntry.name: rbbSubEntry
rbbSubEntry.description: This object defines the individual rows in the subscription table (rbbSubTable)

rbbSubVendor.name: rbbSubVendor
rbbSubVendor.description: The Vendor part of the index that uniquely identifies this CPE

rbbSubModel.name: rbbSubModel
rbbSubModel.description: The Model part of the index that uniquely identifies a CPE

rbbSubSerialNumber.name: rbbSubSerialNumber
rbbSubSerialNumber.description: The serial number part of the index that uniquely identifies a CPE

rbbSubServiceIdentifier.name: rbbSubServiceIdentifier
rbbSubServiceIdentifier.description: An Index value referring to an entry in the rbbServicesTable. This is the service-side in the customer/service subscription association.

rbbSubVPI.name: rbbSubVPI
rbbSubVPI.description: The virtual path identifier to be used in the establishment of a PVC to a particular service, if the service is PVC- based.

rbbSubVCI.name: rbbSubVCI
rbbSubVCI.description: The virtual circuit identifier to be used in the establishment of a PVC to a particular service, if the service is PVC-based.

rbbSubAddr.name: rbbSubAddr
rbbSubAddr.description: The end-system address to be used in the establishment of an SVC to a particular service, if the service is SVC-based.

rbbSubStatus.name: rbbSubStatus
rbbSubStatus.description: The current status of this subscription, currently defined as up, down, or suspended.

rbbCPETable.name: rbbCPETable
rbbCPETable.description: This table contains a sequence of rows where each row describes a particular CPE that has identified itself to the management framework.

rbbCPEEntry.name: rbbCPEEntry
rbbCPEEntry.description: This object defines the individual rows in the CPE table (rbbCPETable)

rbbCPEAuthValue.name: rbbCPEAuthValue
rbbCPEAuthValue.description: A unique identifier that uniquely identifies a particular customer or end-user

rbbCPEVendorOID.name: rbbCPEVendorOID
rbbCPEVendorOID.description: A unique object identifier that identifies a particular CPE vendor

rbbCPEStatus.name: rbbCPEStatus
rbbCPEStatus.description: An integer enumeration that identifies the current status of the CPE device

rbbCPESubCount.name: rbbCPESubCount
rbbCPESubCount.description: An integer value representing the number of service subscriptions that exist in the subscription table for this customer

rbbCPESubAggrSpeed.name: rbbCPESubAggrSpeed
rbbCPESubAggrSpeed.description: The total aggregate bandwidth required by all active subscriptions for this CPE customer.

rbbCPECustContact.name: rbbCPECustContact
rbbCPECustContact.description: The email address for the individual at the customer premises that is responsible for the broadband service.

rbbCPESerialNumber.name: rbbCPESerialNumber
rbbCPESerialNumber.description: The unique hardware address or serial number associated with the CPE

rbbCPETrapEnable.name: rbbCPETrapEnable
rbbCPETrapEnable.description: A boolean value representing whether or not service-related traps are enabled or disabled for this CPE device.

rbbCPECurrentImage.name: rbbCPECurrentImage
rbbCPECurrentImage.description: A URL string pointing to the current image that is installed in this particular CPE/customer site

rbbVendorTable.name: rbbVendorTable
rbbVendorTable.description: Vendor table describing types of CPE supported, and associated CPE management details.

rbbVendorEntry.name: rbbVendorEntry
rbbVendorEntry.description: Each row describes a particular vendor model of CPE

rbbVendorOID.name: rbbVendorOID
rbbVendorOID.description: A unique object identifier value associated with a particular vendor of CPE

rbbVendorModel.name: rbbVendorModel
rbbVendorModel.description: A human-readable string representing the model number for a particular vendor's CPE device

rbbVendorImageURL.name: rbbVendorImageURL
rbbVendorImageURL.description: A URL string representing the most current version of firmware available for this CPE model

rbbSubNotify.name: rbbSubNotify
rbbSubNotify.description: This notification indicates that a new subscription has been added to, or when a subscription has been deleted from the rbbSubTable in the rbbSubGroup. The notification includes which specific index was added so that the manager does not have to implement a search for changes.
